cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.OS, cs.DS, cs.PL

This paper discusses consistency models in data stores, which are typically used in distributed systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). However, since data stores are often used in conjunction with databases, cs.DB (Databases) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the implementation of data stores in operating systems, which suggests cs.OS (Operating Systems) as another possible category. Additionally, since data structures and algorithms are used to implement data stores, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category. Finally, since the paper discusses the implementation of data stores in application processes, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a possible category.
